---
---
<section
  data-test="problem-section"
  class="w-full py-20 px-4"
  style="background-color:var(--surface);"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-center" style="color:var(--text);">
      AI coding without a spec is chaos
    </h2>
    <p class="text-center mb-12 text-lg" style="color:var(--text-muted);">
      Prompting AI agents to build software leads to inconsistency, drift, and untestable output.
    </p>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border" style="background-color:var(--bg);border-color:var(--border);">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-3">🎲</div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2" style="color:var(--text);">Non-deterministic</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--text-muted);">Every agent run produces different output. No guarantee the same feature works tomorrow.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border" style="background-color:var(--bg);border-color:var(--border);">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-3">🌀</div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2" style="color:var(--text);">Spec drift</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--text-muted);">Without a source of truth, agents hallucinate requirements and build the wrong thing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border" style="background-color:var(--bg);border-color:var(--border);">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-3">🔍</div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2" style="color:var(--text);">Unverifiable</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--text-muted);">How do you know if an AI-built feature is correct? Without spec-driven tests, you can't.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
